RDot v0.9b — GraphViz class diagrams for Ruby

Author: Ivan Shikhalev <shikhalev@gmail.com>

License: GNU General Public License, see COPYING

Usage: rdot [options] [LIBS]
    -h, -?, --help                   Show this help.
    -I, --info=[INFO]                Show program's information — set:
                                     	'about' — title with version;
                                     	'author' — author's name with e-mail;
                                     	'license' — license with URL;
                                     	'usage' — command line options;
                                     	'version' — program's version.
                                     or one of predefs:
                                     	'all' <=> 'about,author,license,usage';
                                     	'help' <=> 'about,usage';
                                     	'info' (or nothing) <=> 'about,author,license'.
        --about                      Show program's title.
        --author                     Show program's author.
    -L, --license                    Show program's license.
        --usage                      Show command line options.
    -V, --version                    Show program's version.
    -x, -p, --exclude=LIBS           Exclude libraries from processing.
        --preload
    -i, -l, --include, --input=LIBS  Include libraries to processing.
        --load
    -o, --output=[FILE]              Send output to file instead of stdout.
                                     'rdot.dot' if not specified.
    -t, --title=TITLE                Set title of class diagram.
        --color-module=COLOR         Specify color for highlight module nodes.
                                     Color may by in #RRGGBB form or one of listed at
                                     	http://graphviz.org/doc/info/colors.html.
        --color-module-preloaded=COLOR
                                     Color for highlight preloaded modules.
        --color-class=COLOR          Color for class nodes.
        --color-class-evaluated=COLOR
                                     Color for evaluated classes.
        --color-class-preloaded=COLOR
                                     Color for preloaded classes.
        --color-exception=COLOR      Color for exception classes.
        --color-exception-evaluated=COLOR
                                     Color for evaluated exception classes.
        --color-exception-preloaded=COLOR
                                     Color for preloaded exception classes.
        --color-inherited=COLOR      Color for inheritance edges.
        --color-included=COLOR       Color for inclusion edges.
        --color-extended=COLOR       Color for extension edges.
        --show-protected=[BOOL]      Show public and protected methods.
        --show-private=[BOOL]        Show public, protected and private methods.

Samples:
	see at http://github.com/shikhalev/rdot/downloads
